tr.td: Reverted to version as of 09:48, 18 January 2021 (UTC) The position of the crescent was correct, your version has too many unnecessary shapes.Two circular arcs for the crescent is enough.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 16:46, 19 January 2021

tr.td: Reverted to version as of 22:56, 7 January 2021 (UTC): restored fixed version. In previous version the crescent was at x=300.026, now x=300.000; the distance between outer and inner cicle was 66.239 pixels, now 66.229. Used 2 cirlces for more geometric precision.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 09:48, 18 January 2021

tr.td: Added more decimal places to the previous 313/260 bytes code to improve precision . Other shapes are unnecessary.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 22:56, 7 January 2021

tr.td: Reverted to version as of 00:42, 7 January 2021 (UTC) Green must be a composition of equal yellow and blue having» as per official text. (source: http://crwflags.com/fotw/flags/dz.html)

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 21:53, 7 January 2021

tr.td: Reverted to version as of 15:26, 6 January 2021 (UTC): restored original color shades because previous color shades was without previous talk-consensus. The previous version was re-uploaded as File:Flag of Algeria (color shades variant).svg.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 15:37, 7 January 2021

tr.td: Fixed color shades according to [https://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/dz.html] (Flags of the World) and [http://www.vexilla-mundi.com/algeria_flag.html] (Vexilla Mundi): Green=Pantone-356C (RGB:0-122-51); Red=Pantone-186C (RGB:200-16-46); see for Pantone-RGB conversion [https://codebeautify.org/pantone-to-rgb-converter]: in previous version slight different. Re-optimized svg code before upload. No other changes.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 00:42, 7 January 2021

tr.td: «Green must be a composition of equal yellow and blue having» as per official text. (source: http://crwflags.com/fotw/flags/dz.html)

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 15:26, 6 January 2021

tr.td: Centered (on X-axis only) the "Crescent": in previous version was 300.096, now 300.000. Fixed geometry for the "Crescent" (simplified its structure: 2 circles in overlapping but without "cut path">>more precision). Fixed geometry for the "Star": in previous version was 135x142 pixels, now 135.677x142.659 pixels>>it is now perfectly circumscribed in an imaginary circle of 150 pixels in diameter. Optimized svg code before upload. No other changes.
